WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.387 --> 00:00:13.930 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Let's get going.

00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:15.849 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
What do you wanna do first?

00:00:15.932 --> 00:00:19.602 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Well, let's see.
What is there in Tottori?

00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:21.813 position:50% align:center
No big coffee chains,
just local brews!

00:00:21.896 --> 00:00:26.234 position:50% align:center
Crab rich, cash poor!
Welcome to Tottori Prefecture!

00:00:26.317 --> 00:00:29.112 position:50% align:center
'Kay, that's weird.
What was with that guy?

00:00:29.195 --> 00:00:32.282 position:50% align:center
Are you being serious?
You don't know?

00:00:32.365 --> 00:00:34.242 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNOR] No convenience
stores? No problem.

00:00:34.325 --> 00:00:36.453 position:50% align:center
Who needs those?
We don't got 'em.

00:00:36.536 --> 00:00:38.329 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:00:38.413 --> 00:00:40.457 position:50% align:center
He's a real big shot.

00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:43.877 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] We should probably
hit the sand dunes first.

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:47.255 position:50% align:center
Says here that we can paraglide
or go sandboarding!

00:00:47.339 --> 00:00:49.507 position:50% align:center
Guess you like the
active stuff, huh?

00:00:49.591 --> 00:00:50.467 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah.

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:52.802 position:50% align:center
All solo activities, I noticed.

00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:55.472 position:50% align:center
You're going full loner
in Tottori, too!

00:00:55.555 --> 00:00:58.850 position:50% align:center
And you won't shut up
no matter where we go.

00:00:58.933 --> 00:01:00.769 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
So, how're we gettin' around?

00:01:00.852 --> 00:01:03.480 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] I dunno. We'll take
the bus or something.

00:01:03.563 --> 00:01:05.273 position:50% align:center
Heh.

00:01:09.319 --> 00:01:11.446 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI gasps, screams]

00:01:12.989 --> 00:01:14.032 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys!

00:01:14.115 --> 00:01:14.991 position:50% align:center
Yo!

00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:16.242 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Itsuhito!

00:01:16.326 --> 00:01:17.869 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
And Ami!

00:02:50.837 --> 00:02:53.048 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] How crazy that
you're both here, too!

00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:56.885 position:50% align:center
Dad wanted me to take a
summer break. And then...

00:02:56.968 --> 00:02:59.429 position:50% align:center
I was thinking of taking a trip
when she ran into me

00:02:59.512 --> 00:03:01.931 position:50% align:center
and suggested meeting
up with you two here.

00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.725 position:50% align:center
Seemed like a plan.

00:03:03.808 --> 00:03:08.355 position:50% align:center
I'll say! I feel bad, though.
You guys renting a car and all.

00:03:08.438 --> 00:03:09.731 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
Nah, totally fine.

00:03:09.814 --> 00:03:11.858 position:50% align:center
You have a thoughtful
side, Sakaki!

00:03:11.941 --> 00:03:13.735 position:50% align:center
That's a terrific trait.

00:03:13.818 --> 00:03:16.905 position:50% align:center
The rest of you is iffy,
but at least there's that.

00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:19.032 position:50% align:center
Please, enough with
the compliments!

00:03:19.115 --> 00:03:21.868 position:50% align:center
Wasn't really a compliment.

00:03:21.951 --> 00:03:24.204 position:50% align:center
[ASAI] It's definitely more
efficient to travel by car,

00:03:24.287 --> 00:03:25.372 position:50% align:center
don't you think?

00:03:25.455 --> 00:03:27.415 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
It's cushier than I imagined.

00:03:27.499 --> 00:03:31.378 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] Right? A rental car is
a must if you want real freedom.

00:03:31.461 --> 00:03:33.838 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Spoken like a seasoned traveler.

00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.632 position:50% align:center
You know me!

00:03:35.715 --> 00:03:37.133 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI]
So went our story.

00:03:37.217 --> 00:03:39.928 position:50% align:center
But our trip here
serves another purpose.

00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.888 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
That's right. Hana and Sakurai,

00:03:41.971 --> 00:03:43.556 position:50% align:center
vacationing alone together.

00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:45.433 position:50% align:center
I want their relationship
to be untouched

00:03:45.517 --> 00:03:48.478 position:50% align:center
by other hands, but even
I couldn't stay away!

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:50.772 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] We've been watching
over their progress thus far

00:03:50.855 --> 00:03:54.234 position:50% align:center
and it's right on track. We have
a duty to see this through.

00:03:54.317 --> 00:03:55.819 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
And we get front-row seats!

00:03:55.902 --> 00:03:59.364 position:50% align:center
What a treat! Not to mention
a trip to Tottori.

00:03:59.447 --> 00:04:03.201 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] Pure coincidence,
of course, but should be fun.

00:04:03.284 --> 00:04:06.788 position:50% align:center
[BOTH] These two still don't
even know the <i>real</i> Tottori!

00:04:06.871 --> 00:04:08.415 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI gasps]
A convenience store.

00:04:08.498 --> 00:04:11.376 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Hey, yeah!
So, they do have them.

00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:21.344 position:50% align:center
[GROUP gasping]

00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.097 position:50% align:center
They really are spectacular
in person, aren't they?

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:27.308 position:50% align:center
Agreed. Man, what
a beautiful sight!

00:04:27.392 --> 00:04:30.562 position:50% align:center
[GUIDE A] The sand dunes measure
2.4 kilometers, north to south.

00:04:30.645 --> 00:04:32.564 position:50% align:center
Sixteen kilometers east to west.

00:04:32.647 --> 00:04:34.816 position:50% align:center
Most people don't realize
they're the largest sand dunes

00:04:34.899 --> 00:04:37.861 position:50% align:center
in Japan that are actually
accessible to people.

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:40.405 position:50% align:center
The dune right in front there
is called the Horse's Back.

00:04:40.488 --> 00:04:42.991 position:50% align:center
It measures about
50 meters high.

00:04:43.074 --> 00:04:45.118 position:50% align:center
It's a popular tourist spot
because from its peak,

00:04:45.201 --> 00:04:46.369 position:50% align:center
you can see the all of the dunes

00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:48.705 position:50% align:center
and take in amazing views
of the Japan Sea.

00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:51.708 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI laughs]
Whoa, nice!

00:04:51.791 --> 00:04:53.126 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Heh!

00:04:53.209 --> 00:04:56.254 position:50% align:center
Hey, Sakurai! What do you
say we race to the water?

00:04:56.338 --> 00:04:58.548 position:50% align:center
You're on!

00:04:58.631 --> 00:05:01.676 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] If I win, you owe me
a nashi pear fro-yo!

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:06.014 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] And if I win,
you owe me a coffee ice cream!

00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50% align:center
Okay, ready... set...

00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:09.851 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Go!

00:05:09.934 --> 00:05:12.729 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI yells]

00:05:14.272 --> 00:05:17.942 position:50% align:center
[gasping] The sand really grabs
the feet. This is rough!

00:05:18.026 --> 00:05:19.861 position:50% align:center
Suddenly regretting these shoes!

00:05:19.944 --> 00:05:22.572 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
What's up, bud?

00:05:22.655 --> 00:05:24.866 position:50% align:center
Hey! What the heck is that?

00:05:24.949 --> 00:05:27.702 position:50% align:center
A sandboard, just like
you were talking about!

00:05:27.786 --> 00:05:29.829 position:50% align:center
I decided to reserve
one for myself!

00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:31.206 position:50% align:center
That's not fair!

00:05:31.289 --> 00:05:32.624 position:50% align:center
Ha! Whatever!

00:05:32.707 --> 00:05:35.251 position:50% align:center
You know that a contest begins
way before it starts!

00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:36.586 position:50% align:center
Catch ya on the flip side!

00:05:36.670 --> 00:05:38.338 position:50% align:center
Dammit!

00:05:38.421 --> 00:05:40.256 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI laughs]

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:43.468 position:50% align:center
Might as well give up,
'cause you'll never catch me!

00:05:43.551 --> 00:05:44.886 position:50% align:center
Ohh...

00:05:46.012 --> 00:05:49.224 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Cheater! Hold it right there!

00:05:49.307 --> 00:05:52.185 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI panting]

00:05:52.268 --> 00:05:55.271 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI yells]

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:57.273 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI gasping]

00:05:57.357 --> 00:06:02.362 position:50% align:center
Yeah! I win, you loser.

00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:08.243 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] A competition against
this beautiful backdrop?

00:06:08.326 --> 00:06:11.413 position:50% align:center
Seriously, have you no soul?

00:06:12.414 --> 00:06:14.207 position:50% align:center
I admit, I admire your nerve,

00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:17.836 position:50% align:center
whining about losing
when it was your idea.

00:06:17.919 --> 00:06:20.922 position:50% align:center
Still, it really is beautiful.

00:06:21.006 --> 00:06:23.967 position:50% align:center
Makes our race seem
kind of insignificant.

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.594 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI panting]
So, I don't owe you, then?

00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:27.595 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Nah, you do.

00:06:27.679 --> 00:06:29.305 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI grumbles]

00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:36.271 position:50% align:center
[AKKYUN] Excuse me!
Could you take our picture?

00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.772 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Oh, sure.

00:06:37.856 --> 00:06:39.482 position:50% align:center
[MIHO]
Thanks so much!

00:06:40.442 --> 00:06:42.318 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Tottori!

00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:46.364 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI chuckles nervously]

00:06:46.448 --> 00:06:48.408 position:50% align:center
[AKKYUN]
We appreciate it!

00:06:48.491 --> 00:06:51.036 position:50% align:center
Oh, Ooxy-pie, you look
so cool in this shot!

00:06:51.119 --> 00:06:53.872 position:50% align:center
And you are so cute, Miho-Miho!

00:06:53.955 --> 00:06:57.042 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI grunts]
Okay, shall we?

00:06:57.125 --> 00:07:00.086 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI groans]
But I can't walk.

00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:03.048 position:50% align:center
Oh, fine then, you win.

00:07:03.131 --> 00:07:06.885 position:50% align:center
Thankfully, somehow, I still
have some strength left.

00:07:06.968 --> 00:07:08.553 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:07:08.636 --> 00:07:10.972 position:50% align:center
[BOTH chuckle]

00:07:15.018 --> 00:07:16.311 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
It's so round!

00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:18.605 position:50% align:center
Japan's oldest circular
school building,

00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.190 position:50% align:center
originally a primary school.

00:07:20.273 --> 00:07:22.484 position:50% align:center
Allow me to tell you about it.

00:07:22.567 --> 00:07:24.277 position:50% align:center
The structure used
to be dilapidated,

00:07:24.361 --> 00:07:26.112 position:50% align:center
and it was due to be torn down.

00:07:26.196 --> 00:07:28.031 position:50% align:center
But the citizens who
wanted it to remain

00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:30.158 position:50% align:center
spurred the officials
into action.

00:07:30.241 --> 00:07:33.828 position:50% align:center
And so the building was
reborn as a museum!

00:07:33.912 --> 00:07:35.747 position:50% align:center
Now it has various
local specialties

00:07:35.830 --> 00:07:37.791 position:50% align:center
on display for your pleasure.

00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:39.918 position:50% align:center
Regional specialties, huh?

00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:41.670 position:50% align:center
What, like nashi pears?

00:07:41.753 --> 00:07:44.255 position:50% align:center
Can't forget Matsuba
snow crabs.

00:07:45.382 --> 00:07:47.509 position:50% align:center
[ASAI laughs]

00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:56.851 position:50% align:center
Look at these figurines!

00:07:56.935 --> 00:07:58.895 position:50% align:center
Yeah, and the Nendoroids, too.

00:07:58.978 --> 00:08:00.939 position:50% align:center
[GUIDE A]
Tottori is the Manga Prefecture,

00:08:01.022 --> 00:08:03.191 position:50% align:center
the birthplace of
many manga artists,

00:08:03.274 --> 00:08:06.277 position:50% align:center
and it's home to a terrific
figurine factory, as well!

00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:08.321 position:50% align:center
In other words,
manga and figurines

00:08:08.405 --> 00:08:11.324 position:50% align:center
are indeed local
Tottori specialties!

00:08:11.408 --> 00:08:14.411 position:50% align:center
[ASAI gasps] I'm starting
to get that feeling, yes.

00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.913 position:50% align:center
[SAKAKI] I could hang
around here all day!

00:08:16.996 --> 00:08:18.915 position:50% align:center
Oh, these are adorable!

00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:21.626 position:50% align:center
Sakurai, wanna buy me
something as a souvenir?

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:23.378 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Seriously?
You're getting four?

00:08:23.461 --> 00:08:26.965 position:50% align:center
They look like four sisters,
so I don't wanna separate them!

00:08:27.048 --> 00:08:30.468 position:50% align:center
Oh! Come on! Different versions!
Double or nothin'!

00:08:30.552 --> 00:08:32.762 position:50% align:center
Okay, I vote nothing!

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:33.680 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:33.763 --> 00:08:36.766 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Tottori!

00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:38.560 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI grumbles]

00:08:41.187 --> 00:08:45.150 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Hey, a rabbit! And that
"Mistress Himiko" person.

00:08:45.233 --> 00:08:47.193 position:50% align:center
[ASAI]
Okuninushi-no-Mikoto.

00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:49.904 position:50% align:center
Or Onamuji-no-Kami!

00:08:49.988 --> 00:08:52.449 position:50% align:center
[GUIDE A] Okuninushi-no-Mikoto
of the "The White Hare

00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:55.160 position:50% align:center
of Inaba," in enshrined
here at Hakuto Shrine.

00:08:55.243 --> 00:08:57.704 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI chuckles]

00:08:57.787 --> 00:08:59.539 position:50% align:center
[GUIDE A] Because the
deity is famously said

00:08:59.622 --> 00:09:02.542 position:50% align:center
to have healed a hare whose fur
had been torn off by a shark,

00:09:02.625 --> 00:09:04.961 position:50% align:center
the shrine is now revered
mostly for its benefits

00:09:05.045 --> 00:09:08.048 position:50% align:center
to those with skin
diseases and injuries.

00:09:08.131 --> 00:09:09.424 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:11.426 --> 00:09:14.137 position:50% align:center
Sakurai, check it out!
Rabbit cakes!

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:17.390 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Oh! They look tasty!

00:09:17.474 --> 00:09:19.517 position:50% align:center
You gonna introduce me
to your friend?

00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:21.394 position:50% align:center
He's the shop clerk.

00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:23.730 position:50% align:center
She said you'd pay for these.

00:09:23.813 --> 00:09:25.732 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Much obliged, loner-boy!

00:09:25.815 --> 00:09:28.109 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Wait, now it's <i>my</i> treat?

00:09:30.487 --> 00:09:33.031 position:50% align:center
Soft and chewy
and oh-so-delicious!

00:09:33.114 --> 00:09:34.783 position:50% align:center
That's great. Good for you.

00:09:34.866 --> 00:09:37.077 position:50% align:center
Oh, come on, don't be so angry.

00:09:37.160 --> 00:09:40.622 position:50% align:center
Here, you should take some!
There's enough for you, too.

00:09:40.705 --> 00:09:43.083 position:50% align:center
Fine, all right, here goes.

00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:45.919 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI screams]
He's gonna gobble me up!

00:09:47.921 --> 00:09:50.799 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI screaming]
Curse you humans to hell!

00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:53.677 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
No!

00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:56.846 position:50% align:center
Listen, I can't eat like this!
Would you shut up?

00:09:56.930 --> 00:10:00.934 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI] Oh? You're not hungry?
Well! Don't mind if I do!

00:10:01.017 --> 00:10:05.146 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Arg! You just
literally ate half in one bite!

00:10:06.189 --> 00:10:08.525 position:50% align:center
Gimme one more little taste!

00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:11.069 position:50% align:center
Not a chance!

00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:13.154 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:14.656 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
You're wide open!

00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:17.826 position:50% align:center
Ha! I guess inattention
is the greatest foe!

00:10:17.909 --> 00:10:19.327 position:50% align:center
You are the worst.

00:10:19.411 --> 00:10:20.829 position:50% align:center
Isn't it yummy?

00:10:20.912 --> 00:10:22.789 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah, you know it!

00:10:22.872 --> 00:10:23.998 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:10:24.082 --> 00:10:26.001 position:50% align:center
Now just say, "ahh"!

00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:28.336 position:50% align:center
Ahh!

00:10:28.420 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
[AKKYUN]
Aw, you ate half of it!

00:10:30.380 --> 00:10:31.840 position:50% align:center
[MIHO giggles]

00:10:31.923 --> 00:10:33.341 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.220 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Uzaki. You have to
think about what you're doing.

00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:39.389 position:50% align:center
You're driving me insane.

00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:40.390 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Right.

00:10:40.473 --> 00:10:41.474 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Don't look at my mouth!

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:42.600 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI yelps]

00:10:47.063 --> 00:10:48.606 position:50% align:center
Is this it, then?

00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:51.443 position:50% align:center
Yes. Any minute now,
it should happen.

00:10:51.526 --> 00:10:54.279 position:50% align:center
They'll learn the truth
about Tottori.

00:10:55.780 --> 00:10:57.615 position:50% align:center
[clapping]

00:10:59.576 --> 00:11:01.870 position:50% align:center
May our travels continue
without a hitch.

00:11:01.953 --> 00:11:04.831 position:50% align:center
And may Sakurai's loner
ways finally be healed.

00:11:04.914 --> 00:11:07.083 position:50% align:center
I'm not a loner!

00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:09.627 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI gasps] Hey, cool,
look, they have fortunes!

00:11:09.711 --> 00:11:11.504 position:50% align:center
What do you think,
should we see who wins?

00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:12.672 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Would you stop?

00:11:12.756 --> 00:11:16.134 position:50% align:center
It's not a competition.
But I mean, sure.

00:11:16.217 --> 00:11:18.720 position:50% align:center
"Middling Luck"?!
